===[[Etymology]]===

[Orig. the same wort as [[ladanum]], [[ladbdanum]]: cf. F. laudanum, It. [[laudano]], [[ladano]]. See [[Ladanum]].]

===[[Noun]]===

Tincture of opium, used for various medical purposes. &hand; A fluid ounce of American laudanum should contain the soluble matter of one tenth of an ounce [[avoirdupois]] of powdered opium with equal parts of alcohol and water. English laudanum should have ten grains less of opium in the fluid ounce. U. S. Disp. Dutchman's laudanum (Bot.) See under [[Dutchman]].
